modules.description: Provides functions to open and close binary input and output channels that automatically compress and decompress data using LZ4. Works with OCaml's binary channel types and the Marshal module for serializing and deserializing values. Enables efficient, on-the-fly compression of data streams during marshaling and unmarshaling operations.

Opens binary input and output channels on files, automatically compressing and decompressing data using LZ4 through a background process and named pipes. Works with file paths and standard in/out channel types. Used for efficiently reading and writing large files with transparent compression, such as log files or data backups.
